{
  "texts": [
    "Various types of time-ordering products discussed in the literature and their relations to Schwinger-Keldysh time-folds.",
    "For illustrative purposes, each panel only shows a three time-fold contour, with the generalization to an arbitrary number of time-folds following the same obvious patterns.",
    "Top left: product of time-ordered products T. Top right: product of anti-time-ordered products T. Bottom left: mixed product of time-and anti-time ordered products.",
    "Bottom right: product of retarded products R. As before, time is going from right to left in each panel.",
    "(.49b) Note that the overall sign flipped from (4.48a) to (4.49b) because there are two vertices and one propagator on the left of the cut."
  ]
}